\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Phase-1 closed-form ablations on the 39-panel NLP grid (50\%-depth layer).} Same fresh nonlinear probe ($h=128$, 200 SGD steps, patience 3) is trained on each post-erasure representation. \emph  {LEACE} is the affine LEACE eraser. \emph  {LEACE\,+\,CovMatch K=2} additionally projects out the top-2 eigenvectors of $\Delta \Sigma = \Sigma _{+} - \Sigma _{-}$ (rank-3 closed-form erasure total). \emph  {TanGCE\textsuperscript  {++}{}} is the proposed full pipeline (LEACE + CovMatch K=2 preprocessing + iterative tangent loop, $\varepsilon {=}0.1$); we report the best $|S{-}\text  {floor}|$ trajectory step subject to $\Delta Y \geq -5$pp. NL = nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower is better; floor is the per-panel majority class). $\Delta Y$ in pp on the control task. Bold marks the row's NL minimum.}}{21}{table.caption.35}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:leace_vs_tangce_nlp}{{4}{21}{\textbf {Phase-1 closed-form ablations on the 39-panel NLP grid (50\%-depth layer).} Same fresh nonlinear probe ($h=128$, 200 SGD steps, patience 3) is trained on each post-erasure representation. \emph {LEACE} is the affine LEACE eraser. \emph {LEACE\,+\,CovMatch K=2} additionally projects out the top-2 eigenvectors of $\Delta \Sigma = \Sigma _{+} - \Sigma _{-}$ (rank-3 closed-form erasure total). \emph {\TanGCEpp {}} is the proposed full pipeline (LEACE + CovMatch K=2 preprocessing + iterative tangent loop, $\varepsilon {=}0.1$); we report the best $|S{-}\text {floor}|$ trajectory step subject to $\Delta Y \geq -5$pp. NL = nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower is better; floor is the per-panel majority class). $\Delta Y$ in pp on the control task. Bold marks the row's NL minimum}{table.caption.35}{}}
